---
/**
 * §01 protocol — park + rememberForTurn vs sandbox escalation one-shot.
 */
---

<svg
  class="pre-flow"
  viewBox="0 0 868 300"
  xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"
  role="presentation"
  focusable="false"
>
  <defs>
    <marker
      id="pre-arrow"
      viewBox="0 0 10 10"
      refX="9"
      refY="5"
      markerWidth="6"
      markerHeight="6"
      orient="auto-start-reverse"
    >
      <path d="M 0 1.5 L 9 5 L 0 8.5 Z" fill="var(--accent)"></path>
    </marker>
  </defs>

  <text class="pre-kicker pre-stage pre-stage--0" x="8" y="20" fill="var(--accent)">
    PROTOCOL · PARK · REMEMBER-FOR-TURN ≠ ONE-SHOT ESCALATION
  </text>
  <line
    class="pre-stage pre-stage--0"
    x1="8"
    y1="34"
    x2="860"
    y2="34"
    stroke="var(--hair)"
    stroke-width="1"
  ></line>

  <g class="pre-stage pre-stage--1" transform="translate(8,48)">
    <rect width="200" height="120" rx="1" fill="var(--bg)" stroke="var(--hair)"></rect>
    <text class="pre-idx" x="14" y="26" fill="var(--accent)">PROMPT</text>
    <text class="pre-title" x="14" y="56" fill="var(--ink)">Park Promise</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="84" fill="var(--mute)">turn-scoped registry</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="106" fill="var(--mute)">Run keeps identity</text>
  </g>

  <path
    class="pre-stage pre-stage--1"
    d="M 220 108 H 252"
    stroke="var(--accent)"
    stroke-width="1.25"
    fill="none"
    marker-end="url(#pre-arrow)"
  ></path>

  <g class="pre-stage pre-stage--2" transform="translate(260,48)">
    <rect width="288" height="120" rx="1" fill="var(--soft)" stroke="var(--accent)"></rect>
    <rect width="288" height="2" fill="var(--accent)"></rect>
    <text class="pre-idx" x="14" y="26" fill="var(--accent)">REMEMBER ALLOWED</text>
    <text class="pre-title" x="14" y="56" fill="var(--ink)">scopeKey → turn set</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="84" fill="var(--mute)">sibling parks auto-allow</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="106" fill="var(--mute)">until turn end</text>
  </g>

  <g class="pre-stage pre-stage--3" transform="translate(568,48)">
    <rect width="292" height="120" rx="1" fill="var(--bg)" stroke="var(--hair)"></rect>
    <rect width="292" height="2" fill="var(--accent)" opacity="0.55"></rect>
    <text class="pre-idx" x="14" y="26" fill="var(--accent)">ONE-SHOT GRANT</text>
    <text class="pre-title" x="14" y="56" fill="var(--ink)">rememberForTurn FORBIDDEN</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="84" fill="var(--mute)">bind command/cwd · TTL</text>
    <text class="pre-mute" x="14" y="106" fill="var(--mute)">consume once · mismatch fails</text>
  </g>

  <text class="pre-foot pre-stage pre-stage--4" x="8" y="210" fill="var(--mute)">
    Sandbox escalation and additional-permission proposals set rememberForTurnAllowed=false. Carrying rememberForTurn on the response throws.
  </text>
  <text class="pre-foot pre-stage pre-stage--4" x="8" y="234" fill="var(--mute)">
    Approval is not a standing unsandboxed mode. OS transform still lives in #sandbox — orthogonal to park/remember.
  </text>
  <text class="pre-foot pre-stage pre-stage--4" x="8" y="268" fill="var(--mute)">
    Turn end rejects still-parked requests — never silent allow.
  </text>
</svg>

<style>
  .pre-flow {
    font-family: var(--sans);
  }
  .pre-kicker {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10.5px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  }
  .pre-idx {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .pre-title {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 14px;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
  .pre-mute {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 11px;
  }
  .pre-foot {
    font-family: var(--serif);
    font-size: 12.5px;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: no-preference) {
    .pre-stage {
      opacity: 0;
      animation: pre-fade 0.55s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards;
    }
    .pre-stage--0 {
      animation-delay: 0.04s;
    }
    .pre-stage--1 {
      animation-delay: 0.14s;
    }
    .pre-stage--2 {
      animation-delay: 0.28s;
    }
    .pre-stage--3 {
      animation-delay: 0.4s;
    }
    .pre-stage--4 {
      animation-delay: 0.52s;
    }
    @keyframes pre-fade {
      from {
        opacity: 0;
      }
      to {
        opacity: 1;
      }
    }
  }
  @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
    .pre-stage {
      opacity: 1;
      animation: none;
    }
  }
</style>
